        {
            "name": "Flea Swarm",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [],
            "text": "Flea swarms roil across city streets and rural hinterlands in a hissing, scraping scrabble, draining blood from any creatures unfortunate enough to cross their path.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Animal</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a></u>)</b>: DC 20",
            "source": {
                "name": "Pathfinder #151: The Show Must Go On",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq021x1"
                },
                "page": 83
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Flea",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Flea Allies",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "Flea swarms and giant fleas make for natural pets and monstrous minions for creatures who live in areas of filth and concentrated populations. <a aonid=\"55\" game-obj=\"MonsterFamilies\">Goblins</a> and <a aonid=\"58\" game-obj=\"MonsterFamilies\">gremlins</a> are unperturbed by fleas\u2019 disturbing physiologies and are unfazed (though not necessarily unaffected) by the diseases these vermin carry. <a aonid=\"105\" game-obj=\"MonsterFamilies\">Ratfolk</a> have been known to tame giant fleas for use as mounts, and urban-dwelling <a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Classes\">druids</a> whose magic focuses on blight or disease naturally find much to like about the flea swarms they frequently summon.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Pathfinder #151: The Show Must Go On",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq021x1"
                        },
                        "page": 83
                    },
                    "subtype": "related_creatures",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Related Creatures",
                    "image": "Sidebar_4_RelatedCreatures.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Fleas are little more than a nuisance in most circumstances, but can be lethal when they grow to monstrous proportions or gather in enormous swarms.",
            "source": {
                "name": "Pathfinder #151: The Show Must Go On",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq021x1"
                },
                "page": 83
            }
